link: Vaclav Kotesovec, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..20000
mathematica: nmax = 100; s = 1 + x; Do[s*=Sum[Binomial[k, j]*x^(j*k^2), {j, 0, Floor[nmax/k^2] + 1}]; s = Select[Expand[s], Exponent[#, x] <= nmax &];, {k, 2, nmax}]; CoefficientList[s, x]
